.TH man_3_printf

.SH NAME
.B _printf: Sends a formatted output to the screen.

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"
.br
int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
Using the _printf function we can write data to the standard output device (screen). The _printf function can write any combination of numeric values, single characters and character strings. 

The printf function transports data from memory to the screen, and returns the number of characters written.

.B Conversion specifiers
.br
A character that specifies the type of conversion to be applied.
.br 
The conversion specifiers and their meanings are:
.TP
c - Print ARGUMENT of character type

.TP
s - Print ARGUMENT of string type

.TP
%% - Prints a single %

.TP
d - Print ARGUMENT of decimal type

.TP
i - Print ARGUMENT of type integer

.SH RETURN VALUE
If the function completes successfully, it returns the number of characters printed.
.br
Otherwise it returns -1.


.SH AUTHOR
.B Written by Charly Barrio and Lucas Soria.
